00:03:21.170 --> 00:03:25.010
So about photon states.

00:03:25.010 --> 00:03:29.980
Well, photon states have to do
with electromagnetic fields.

00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:31.980
That's electric and
magnetic fields.

00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:34.200
And one important
quantity that you

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:40.020
know about the electromagnetic
fields is the energy.

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:42.800
If you have an electromagnetic
field, you have an energy.

00:03:42.800 --> 00:03:45.660
And remember, energies have
to do with Hamiltonians.

00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:47.930
So we're going to
try to do a quantum

00:03:47.930 --> 00:03:50.500
description of the
electromagnetic field.

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:55.210
Therefore, knowing the energy
would be a good place to start.

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:58.570
So the energy, as you know,
in an electromagnetic field

00:03:58.570 --> 00:04:03.620
goes like e squared times
some epsilon and b squared.

00:04:03.620 --> 00:04:05.610
And you add the two of them.

00:04:05.610 --> 00:04:07.140
So here we go.

00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:09.340
Let me write a precise formula.

00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:13.830
The energy is equal
to 1/2 the integral

00:04:13.830 --> 00:04:24.040
over volume, epsilon 0,
the electric field squared,

00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:27.040
plus c squared times the
magnetic field squared.

00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:35.695
So this is our energy.

00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:41.300
And we're going
to try to describe

00:04:41.300 --> 00:04:45.640
a configuration of
electromagnetic fields.

00:04:45.640 --> 00:04:50.190
We will to focus on one mode
of the electromagnetic field.

00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:55.540
So I will imagine I have some
sort of cavity, finite volume.

00:04:55.540 --> 00:04:58.850
And in there I have one
electromagnetic field,

00:04:58.850 --> 00:05:06.110
what you usually called in
802 or in 8022 or 807 a wave.

00:05:06.110 --> 00:05:09.690
A single wave with some
wavelength, some frequency,

00:05:09.690 --> 00:05:11.420
and that's all we have.

00:05:11.420 --> 00:05:13.970
So we're going to
simplify to the case

00:05:13.970 --> 00:05:18.170
where we have a single one
consistent with Maxwell's

00:05:18.170 --> 00:05:23.950
equations and some boundary
conditions that we need not

00:05:23.950 --> 00:05:26.500
worry about.

00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:33.120
And I will normalize them
as follows with a V in here.

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:37.590
That this is the
volume of the system.

00:05:37.590 --> 00:05:38.240
So, volume.

00:05:42.550 --> 00:05:45.250
And that could be the
volume of the cavity that

00:05:45.250 --> 00:05:47.220
has this electromagnetic field.

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:49.090
Or some large box.

00:05:49.090 --> 00:05:53.550
Or you can let it almost be
infinite and work with that

00:05:53.550 --> 00:05:55.130
as well.

00:05:55.130 --> 00:05:59.210
So we'll have a wave.

00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:01.360
Omega would be the frequency.

00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:07.140
K is omega over c for
a electromagnetic wave.

00:06:07.140 --> 00:06:13.480
So we'll have this
times omega sine

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:19.250
of kz, a spatial distribution.

00:06:19.250 --> 00:06:22.580
And there will be a function
of time, as you know.

00:06:22.580 --> 00:06:24.570
But this function
of time, I want

00:06:24.570 --> 00:06:30.150
to leave it a little ambiguous
at this moment-- or, general.

00:06:30.150 --> 00:06:31.470
Not ambiguous, general.

00:06:31.470 --> 00:06:37.420
So I'll call it q of t,
some function of time

00:06:37.420 --> 00:06:38.165
to be determined.

00:06:41.020 --> 00:06:44.900
There's going to be an
electromagnetic and magnetic

00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:47.442
component to this field, By.

00:06:47.442 --> 00:06:51.320
c times By will also
depend on z and t

00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:54.050
and will have the
same pre-factor.

00:06:54.050 --> 00:06:55.820
I put the c here.

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:59.760
So your c squared b
squared also works well.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:02.260
Epsilon 0 v.

00:07:02.260 --> 00:07:10.105
This time I'll put another
function, p of t cosine of kz.

00:07:13.630 --> 00:07:18.790
It's another function of time
and I just call them that way.

00:07:18.790 --> 00:07:20.996
There is a question there.

00:07:20.996 --> 00:07:25.830
STUDENT: Why is your frequency
outside your function of time?

00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:30.220
PROFESSOR: It's just
another constant here.

00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:32.000
STUDENT: What would
that mean then?

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:34.770
PROFESSOR: No particular
meaning to it.

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:40.840
At this moment,
whatever this constant

00:07:40.840 --> 00:07:43.950
is you would say
probably it's useful

00:07:43.950 --> 00:07:46.410
because you somehow
wanted the q here.

00:07:46.410 --> 00:07:48.050
That has some meaning.

00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:51.860
So you probably would put
the same constants here

00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:53.230
in first trial.

00:07:53.230 --> 00:07:55.010
You wouldn't have
this omega here.

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:58.480
But if you put it, this
is just another way

00:07:58.480 --> 00:08:00.720
of changing their own
manifestation of q.

00:08:00.720 --> 00:08:04.980
So it doesn't have a
profound meaning so far.

00:08:07.790 --> 00:08:10.460
Any other questions about this?

00:08:10.460 --> 00:08:13.810
This is and electromagnetic
field configuration.

00:08:13.810 --> 00:08:19.240
And this q of t and p of
t are functions of time.

00:08:19.240 --> 00:08:21.490
You know your
Maxwell's equations.

00:08:21.490 --> 00:08:26.490
And you will check things
related to Maxwell's equations

00:08:26.490 --> 00:08:28.670
for this configuration
in the homework.

00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:35.669
But at this moment,
it's not too crucial.

00:08:35.669 --> 00:08:38.549
The thing that this
important is that we

00:08:38.549 --> 00:08:42.110
can try to calculate
the energy now.

00:08:42.110 --> 00:08:47.560
And if you do it, well, the
squares, the epsilon 0's

00:08:47.560 --> 00:08:49.369
are going to disappear.

00:08:49.369 --> 00:08:50.910
And you're going to
have to integrate

00:08:50.910 --> 00:08:57.980
over the box, this integral of
sine squared of kz or cosine

00:08:57.980 --> 00:08:59.210
squared of kz.

00:08:59.210 --> 00:09:01.400
The functions of
time don't matter--

00:09:01.400 --> 00:09:04.080
this energy could
depend on time.

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:08.570
And the way we've prepared
is when you integrate over

00:09:08.570 --> 00:09:11.970
sine squared of kz,
if the box is big,

00:09:11.970 --> 00:09:16.490
it's a good situation where you
can replace that for 1/2, which

00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:20.070
is the average, and 1/2
for the average of this.

00:09:20.070 --> 00:09:27.180
Or you could define
where the box extends,

00:09:27.180 --> 00:09:30.990
from what values of z to
what other values of z's.

00:09:30.990 --> 00:09:37.390
And so the integral, in fact,
is not any complicated integral.

00:09:37.390 --> 00:09:40.240
And we have
immediately the answer

00:09:40.240 --> 00:09:50.640
that energy is 1/2 p squared
of t plus omega squared q

00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:52.700
squared of t.

00:09:56.890 --> 00:09:59.775
And that was why
this omega was here.

00:10:03.790 --> 00:10:06.090
There's not really much to this.

00:10:06.090 --> 00:10:09.240
Except that when you square
it and you take the integral

00:10:09.240 --> 00:10:12.340
over the volume, you replace
the sine squared by 1/2

00:10:12.340 --> 00:10:13.900
and the cosine squared by 1/2.

00:10:13.900 --> 00:10:17.260
And that's it.

00:10:17.260 --> 00:10:21.340
So actually, the labels
that we've chosen here

00:10:21.340 --> 00:10:23.460
are pretty good.

00:10:23.460 --> 00:10:28.290
This starts to look like
a harmonic oscillator.

00:10:28.290 --> 00:10:32.400
Except that the mass is gone.

00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:39.920
1 over 2m p squared should
be plus 1/2 m omega squared

00:10:39.920 --> 00:10:42.170
q squared.

00:10:42.170 --> 00:10:47.300
So the units are wrong here.

00:10:47.300 --> 00:10:52.240
p squared over 2m
has units of energy.

00:10:52.240 --> 00:10:55.520
But p squared doesn't
have units of energy.

00:10:55.520 --> 00:11:00.760
And 1/2 m omega squared q
squared has units of energy

00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:01.980
but this one doesn't.

00:11:01.980 --> 00:11:08.100
So the units are a little off
for a harmonic oscillator.

00:11:08.100 --> 00:11:14.430
So it's interesting
to notice now.

00:11:14.430 --> 00:11:17.190
But you couldn't
have done better.

00:11:17.190 --> 00:11:21.490
Because photons have no mass.

00:11:21.490 --> 00:11:24.250
And we're trying to describe
the electromagnetic field.

00:11:24.250 --> 00:11:25.350
It has photons.

00:11:25.350 --> 00:11:31.820
So there's no way this could
have showed up a mass there.

00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:34.440
There's no such thing.

00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:37.720
And that's why it
doesn't show up.

00:11:37.720 --> 00:11:40.720
On the other hand,
you can say, well, OK,

00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:46.380
let's see if this makes
a minimum of sense.

00:11:46.380 --> 00:11:48.600
How do we deal with this unit?

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:58.835
So p has units of
square root of energy.

00:12:03.830 --> 00:12:17.072
And q has units of time
times square root of energy.

00:12:17.072 --> 00:12:18.380
Why is that?

00:12:18.380 --> 00:12:21.800
Because omega has
units of 1 over time.

00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:26.510
So q over time
squared is energy.

00:12:26.510 --> 00:12:32.630
So q is t times
square root of energy.

00:12:32.630 --> 00:12:38.420
And therefore p doesn't have the
right units to deserve the name

00:12:38.420 --> 00:12:40.550
p.

00:12:40.550 --> 00:12:44.520
And q doesn't have the right
units to deserve the name q.

00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:53.520
But p times q has the
units of time times energy,

00:12:53.520 --> 00:12:56.145
which are the units of h bar.

00:12:59.330 --> 00:13:01.990
So that's good.

00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:08.110
This p and q have the
right units in some sense.

00:13:08.110 --> 00:13:16.990
So this thing could be viewed
as an inspiration for you.

00:13:16.990 --> 00:13:18.440
And you say at
this moment, well,

00:13:18.440 --> 00:13:23.080
I don't know what is a quantum
of an electromagnetic field.

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:27.220
But here I have a
natural correspondence

00:13:27.220 --> 00:13:30.235
between one mode of
vibration, classical,

00:13:30.235 --> 00:13:34.160
of the electromagnetic field,
and an energy functional

00:13:34.160 --> 00:13:37.780
that looks exactly like
a harmonic oscillator.

00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:46.036
So I will declare these things
to be a Hamiltonian and this p

00:13:46.036 --> 00:13:51.430
of t and q of t to be
the Heisenberg operators

00:13:51.430 --> 00:13:54.580
of the electromagnetic field.

00:13:54.580 --> 00:13:58.720
So what we're saying
now is that I'm

00:13:58.720 --> 00:14:04.840
going to just call
the Hamiltonian 1/2 p

00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:10.050
hat squared plus omega
squared q hat squared.

00:14:13.240 --> 00:14:15.830
This is a time
independent Hamiltonian.

00:14:15.830 --> 00:14:20.020
If you're doing Heisenberg,
it's the same thing

00:14:20.020 --> 00:14:24.790
as the Hamiltonian that
would have p hat square of t

00:14:24.790 --> 00:14:30.270
plus omega q hat squared of t.

00:14:30.270 --> 00:14:36.250
Now, at this moment,
this might sound to you

00:14:36.250 --> 00:14:37.750
just too speculative.

00:14:37.750 --> 00:14:43.890
But you can do a couple of
checks that this is reasonable.

00:14:43.890 --> 00:14:51.050
So one check, remember that the
Hamiltonian-- quantum equations

00:14:51.050 --> 00:14:53.800
of motion, of
Heisenberg operators

00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:57.710
should look like classical
equations of motion.

00:14:57.710 --> 00:15:03.460
So I can now compute
what are the Heisenberg

00:15:03.460 --> 00:15:05.700
equation of motions
for the operators.

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:15.010
Remember something like v
dt of p Heisenberg of t dt

00:15:15.010 --> 00:15:20.670
is related to h
with p Heisenberg.

00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:26.680
And you can calculate the
Heisenberg equations of motion.

00:15:26.680 --> 00:15:29.520
I may have signs wrong here.

00:15:29.520 --> 00:15:33.070
Nevertheless, you know those
for the harmonic oscillator

00:15:33.070 --> 00:15:35.280
and you can write them.

00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:39.600
But you also know
Maxwell's equations.

00:15:39.600 --> 00:15:42.330
And you can plug into
Maxwell's equations.

00:15:42.330 --> 00:15:47.080
And that's one check you will do
in homework, in which you will

00:15:47.080 --> 00:15:49.760
take Maxwell's
equations and see what

00:15:49.760 --> 00:15:52.390
equations you have
for q of t p of t.

00:15:52.390 --> 00:15:55.920
And then they will
be exactly the same

00:15:55.920 --> 00:15:59.700
as the Heisenberg equations
of motion of this Hamiltonian,

00:15:59.700 --> 00:16:03.660
giving you evidence that this
is a reasonable thing to do.

00:16:03.660 --> 00:16:09.710
That we can think of this
dynamical system with q and p

00:16:09.710 --> 00:16:13.260
being quantum operators.

00:16:13.260 --> 00:16:18.480
So let's accept that this is
a Hamiltonian for this quantum

00:16:18.480 --> 00:16:21.280
system that we
want to work with.

00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:28.010
And therefore, write the
operators that we have.

00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:29.300
And what are they?

00:16:29.300 --> 00:16:34.820
Well, we had
formulas with masses.

00:16:34.820 --> 00:16:38.290
But now mass goes to 1.

00:16:38.290 --> 00:16:41.850
So know the units.

00:16:41.850 --> 00:16:46.220
You cannot let in general in a
formula mass going to 1 unless

00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:48.840
you're going to do
something with the units.

00:16:48.840 --> 00:16:54.690
But we agreed already that these
p's and q's have funny units.

00:16:54.690 --> 00:16:58.130
So those units are in fact
consistent with a mass

00:16:58.130 --> 00:17:00.530
that has no units.

00:17:00.530 --> 00:17:03.390
And you can set it equal to 1.

00:17:03.390 --> 00:17:08.869
So I claim that you can take
all the formulas we had with m

00:17:08.869 --> 00:17:14.190
and just put m equals to 1
and nothing would go wrong.

00:17:14.190 --> 00:17:15.770
Nothing goes funny.

00:17:15.770 --> 00:17:18.910
So in particular,
you had an expression

00:17:18.910 --> 00:17:26.050
for x that now is called q terms
of creation and annihilation

00:17:26.050 --> 00:17:34.500
operators and now
that reads-- And you

00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:36.190
have an expression for p.

00:17:41.820 --> 00:17:47.256
And that one reads
now a minus a dagger.

00:17:51.470 --> 00:17:54.680
These formulas used
to have m's in there.

00:17:54.680 --> 00:17:57.180
And I've just set m equals to 1.

00:17:57.180 --> 00:18:00.570
And that should be
the right thing.

00:18:00.570 --> 00:18:04.640
Unit-wise, indeed h bar
omega has units of energy.

00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:09.430
And we claim that p has units of
energy, square root of energy.

00:18:09.430 --> 00:18:11.085
So this is fine.

00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:19.640
So what else do we get
from this Hamiltonian?

00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:23.960
Well, we can write it in
terms of the number operators.

00:18:23.960 --> 00:18:30.890
So this Hamiltonian now,
it's equal to h bar omega

00:18:30.890 --> 00:18:33.410
a dagger a plus 1/2.

00:18:36.470 --> 00:18:42.470
And this is just because this
p and q written in this way

00:18:42.470 --> 00:18:44.530
corresponds to m equals to 1.

00:18:44.530 --> 00:18:48.770
And m doesn't show up
anyway in this formula.

00:18:48.770 --> 00:18:54.930
So no reason to be worried
that anything has gone wrong.

00:18:54.930 --> 00:19:05.200
And this is H equals to h
bar omega, N hat plus 1/2.

00:19:05.200 --> 00:19:09.220
And this is a number operator.

00:19:09.220 --> 00:19:11.880
And then you get
the interpretation,

00:19:11.880 --> 00:19:17.990
the physical interpretation
that if you have states

00:19:17.990 --> 00:19:23.200
