in this direction, as opposed
to going in the other direction.

01:00:17.900 --> 01:00:22.340
So this is a basic confirmation
of what the spin is doing.

01:00:22.340 --> 01:00:26.540
And I want to give
you the general result

01:00:26.540 --> 01:00:29.920
so that you can really
use it more clearly.

01:00:29.920 --> 01:00:33.030
So I think the lights
are gone, so we

01:00:33.030 --> 01:00:35.420
can go to this blackboard.

01:00:35.420 --> 01:00:40.270
First of all, classical picture.

01:00:40.270 --> 01:00:43.310
What is it about
spin procession?

01:00:43.310 --> 01:00:47.870
Is it a quantum phenomenon or a
classical phenomenon, or both?

01:00:47.870 --> 01:00:49.250
Well, it's really both.

01:00:49.250 --> 01:00:51.980
And this idea of
procession, you can get it

01:00:51.980 --> 01:00:54.280
from the classical
picture as well.

01:00:54.280 --> 01:00:55.540
So what do you have?

01:00:55.540 --> 01:01:03.760
If you have a mu in a B
field, you get a torque.

01:01:09.360 --> 01:01:12.890
And that you can easily
convince yourself.

01:01:12.890 --> 01:01:15.820
I'm sure you've done
the computation in 802.

01:01:15.820 --> 01:01:18.440
You have a little
square wire not

01:01:18.440 --> 01:01:20.240
aligned with the magnetic field.

01:01:20.240 --> 01:01:23.110
You calculate the force on one
side, the force on the other.

01:01:23.110 --> 01:01:25.070
You see that there is a torque.

01:01:25.070 --> 01:01:32.295
And the torque is given
by mu cross B. That's enm.

01:01:34.810 --> 01:01:42.170
On the other hand, the rate
of change of angular momentum

01:01:42.170 --> 01:01:43.060
is the torque.

01:01:45.830 --> 01:01:57.430
So this is mu cross B.
But mu is gamma S, so this

01:01:57.430 --> 01:02:15.520
is gamma S cross B. And this
is minus gamma B cross S.

01:02:15.520 --> 01:02:16.380
OK.

01:02:16.380 --> 01:02:26.140
This equation, which I
rewrite it here, ds/dt equals

01:02:26.140 --> 01:02:34.650
minus gamma B cross S,
is a particular case

01:02:34.650 --> 01:02:42.460
of a very famous equation
in classical mechanics,

01:02:42.460 --> 01:02:46.940
and this equation for
a rotating vector.

01:02:46.940 --> 01:03:05.515
If you have a vector,
dx/dt is omega cross x.

01:03:09.680 --> 01:03:13.790
This is the equation
satisfied by a vector

01:03:13.790 --> 01:03:17.670
x that is rotating
with angular frequency

01:03:17.670 --> 01:03:23.710
omega around the axis
defined by the vector omega.

01:03:23.710 --> 01:03:25.430
A famous equation.

01:03:25.430 --> 01:03:32.500
OK, so you have here
omega vector is omega n.

01:03:32.500 --> 01:03:35.430
So here is the direction
of n, the unit vector.

01:03:35.430 --> 01:03:36.630
Here's omega.

01:03:36.630 --> 01:03:40.310
And you have a
vector x over here.

01:03:40.310 --> 01:03:43.560
Then this vector, the
solution of this equation,

01:03:43.560 --> 01:03:50.270
is a vector that is rotating
around omega with the angular

01:03:50.270 --> 01:03:51.860
velocity magnitude of omega.

01:03:54.720 --> 01:03:57.130
In the notes, I just
give a little hint

01:03:57.130 --> 01:03:58.640
of how you derive that.

01:03:58.640 --> 01:04:01.860
But truly speaking,
you guys should

01:04:01.860 --> 01:04:04.870
be able to just
scribble a few notes

01:04:04.870 --> 01:04:08.290
if you don't know the situation
by heart, and convince yourself

01:04:08.290 --> 01:04:10.320
this is true.

01:04:10.320 --> 01:04:16.690
So this equation is
of that form in which

01:04:16.690 --> 01:04:23.750
the omega x is played by
S. Omega is minus gamma B.

01:04:23.750 --> 01:04:30.010
So this defines what is called
the Larmor frequency, which

01:04:30.010 --> 01:04:37.455
is minus gamma B, is
the Larmor frequency.

01:04:45.560 --> 01:04:48.600
Now, this Larmor
frequency is precisely

01:04:48.600 --> 01:04:54.520
that one because
was minus gamma B.

01:04:54.520 --> 01:04:57.470
And here you have
minus gamma B times t.

01:04:57.470 --> 01:05:00.570
Omega times t is the angle.

01:05:00.570 --> 01:05:05.960
So in fact, this is rotating
with a Larmor frequency.

01:05:05.960 --> 01:05:06.930
And there you go.

01:05:06.930 --> 01:05:10.420
In the same blackboard, you
have a classical mechanics

01:05:10.420 --> 01:05:12.810
derivation of the
Larmor frequency

01:05:12.810 --> 01:05:14.900
and a quantum
mechanical derivation

01:05:14.900 --> 01:05:16.730
of the Larmor frequency.

01:05:16.730 --> 01:05:20.700
Again, at the end of the
day, this is no coincidence.

01:05:20.700 --> 01:05:24.380
We've made dynamical
classical variables

01:05:24.380 --> 01:05:30.700
into quantum operators, and we
haven't changed the physics.

01:05:30.700 --> 01:05:33.650
Mu dot B is a classical energy.

01:05:33.650 --> 01:05:38.270
Well, it became Hamiltonian,
and it's doing the right thing.

01:05:38.270 --> 01:05:42.460
So we can now use
the Larmor frequency

01:05:42.460 --> 01:05:46.110
to rewrite the
Hamiltonian, of course.

01:05:46.110 --> 01:05:46.755
It's here.

01:05:50.300 --> 01:05:54.680
So a little bit of
emphasis is worth it.

01:05:54.680 --> 01:06:03.750
Hs is minus mu dot B, and
it's minus gamma B dot S,

01:06:03.750 --> 01:06:13.450
and it's finally equal
to omega L dot S.

01:06:13.450 --> 01:06:17.550
So if somebody gives
you a Hamiltonian

01:06:17.550 --> 01:06:21.070
that at the end of the
day, you can write it

01:06:21.070 --> 01:06:28.270
as some vector dot S, you
already know that for spins,

01:06:28.270 --> 01:06:33.710
that is the Larmor
frequency of rotation.

01:06:33.710 --> 01:06:36.890
It's a very simple thing.

01:06:36.890 --> 01:06:40.140
Hs, something times
S, well that's

01:06:40.140 --> 01:06:45.340
precisely the rotation
frequency for the spin states.

01:06:45.340 --> 01:06:47.200
They will all rotate that way.

01:06:51.360 --> 01:06:55.000
So we can say that the spin
states in this Hamiltonian

01:06:55.000 --> 01:06:59.510
rotate with omega L frequency.

01:06:59.510 --> 01:07:02.180
So that's good.

01:07:02.180 --> 01:07:06.980
That's a general discussion of
precession in a magnetic field.

01:07:06.980 --> 01:07:12.600
But I want to go one more
step in generalization.

01:07:12.600 --> 01:07:15.820
It's a simple step,
but let's just take it.

01:07:15.820 --> 01:07:19.740
So that you see
even more generally

01:07:19.740 --> 01:07:25.045
why any system can be
thought of as a spin system.

01:07:29.640 --> 01:07:31.310
And this is quite practical.

01:07:31.310 --> 01:07:34.150
In fact, it's
probably the best way

01:07:34.150 --> 01:07:39.030
to imagine physically, the
effects of any Hamiltonian.

01:07:39.030 --> 01:07:44.320
So let's consider
time-independent Hamiltonians

01:07:44.320 --> 01:07:50.070
the most general Hamiltonian
for a two-state system.

01:07:50.070 --> 01:07:51.250
How can it be?

01:07:51.250 --> 01:07:54.210
Well, a two-state
system, remember

01:07:54.210 --> 01:07:56.620
two-state system is a word.

01:07:56.620 --> 01:08:03.450
It really means a system
with two basis states.

01:08:03.450 --> 01:08:06.150
Once you have two basis
states, a plus and the minus

01:08:06.150 --> 01:08:08.810
have infinitely many
states, of course.

01:08:08.810 --> 01:08:12.700
But two-state system
is two basis states.

01:08:12.700 --> 01:08:15.330
And therefore, in
the Hamiltonian,

01:08:15.330 --> 01:08:19.930
in this two basis states,
is a 2 by 2 matrix.

01:08:19.930 --> 01:08:22.350
And it's a 2 by 2
Hermitian matrix.

01:08:22.350 --> 01:08:25.710
So there's not too
much it can be.

01:08:25.710 --> 01:08:28.800
In fact, you can have
a constant that I

01:08:28.800 --> 01:08:38.000
will call maybe not the base
notation, g not and g not.

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:39.569
And that's Hermitian.

01:08:39.569 --> 01:08:42.960
It's real constant.

01:08:42.960 --> 01:08:47.620
You can put a g3 and a minus g3.

01:08:47.620 --> 01:08:50.380
That's still Hermitian.

01:08:50.380 --> 01:08:51.790
And that's reasonable.

01:08:51.790 --> 01:08:54.590
There's no reason why this
number should be equal to this.

01:08:54.590 --> 01:08:59.090
So there are two numbers here
that are arbitrary, real.

01:08:59.090 --> 01:09:01.460
And therefore, you can put
them wherever you want.

01:09:01.460 --> 01:09:08.260
And I decided to call one g not
plus g3 and one g not minus g3.

01:09:08.260 --> 01:09:12.760
Here, I can put again an
arbitrary complex number,

01:09:12.760 --> 01:09:15.310
as long as I put here
the complex conjugate.

01:09:15.310 --> 01:09:25.399
So I will call this g1 minus
ig2, and this g1 plus ig2.

01:09:25.399 --> 01:09:28.620
And that's the most
general 2 by 2 Hamiltonian.

01:09:28.620 --> 01:09:32.100
Tonya If those would be
time-dependent functions,

01:09:32.100 --> 01:09:36.680
this is the most general
Hamiltonian ever for a 2

01:09:36.680 --> 01:09:37.430
by 2 system.

01:09:37.430 --> 01:09:39.490
It doesn't get more complicated.

01:09:39.490 --> 01:09:42.399
That's a great
advantage of this.

01:09:42.399 --> 01:09:44.630
But I've written it
in a way that you

01:09:44.630 --> 01:09:47.109
can recognize something.

01:09:47.109 --> 01:09:49.910
You can recognize
that this is g not

01:09:49.910 --> 01:09:56.420
times the identity plus g1 times
sigma 1 plus g2 times sigma

01:09:56.420 --> 01:10:01.390
2 plus g3 times sigma 3.

01:10:01.390 --> 01:10:05.680
And this is because the
Pauli matrices are, together

01:10:05.680 --> 01:10:12.310
with the unit matrix, a
basis for all Hermitian 2

01:10:12.310 --> 01:10:14.500
by 2 matrices.

01:10:14.500 --> 01:10:17.980
So the Pauli matrices
are Hermitian.

01:10:17.980 --> 01:10:19.920
The unit matrix is Hermitian.

01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:22.590
The most general 2
by 2 Hermitian matrix

01:10:22.590 --> 01:10:25.890
is a number times the one
matrix, then number times

01:10:25.890 --> 01:10:29.470
the first part, then number,
second, number, third.

01:10:29.470 --> 01:10:31.840
OK.

01:10:31.840 --> 01:10:35.890
So at this moment, we've got
the most general Hamiltonian.

01:10:35.890 --> 01:10:42.540
And I will write it as g
not times 1 plus g vector

01:10:42.540 --> 01:10:51.340
dot sigma, where g
vector is g1, g2, g3.

01:10:55.910 --> 01:11:03.050
If we write the g
vector as length

01:11:03.050 --> 01:11:07.840
of g, which is
just the letter g,

01:11:07.840 --> 01:11:11.520
shouldn't be confused because
we have g not, g1, g2, g3,

01:11:11.520 --> 01:11:14.430
but we haven't had a
g without an index.

01:11:14.430 --> 01:11:18.760
So g without an index is
going to be the magnitude of g

01:11:18.760 --> 01:11:23.640
vector, and n is going to
be a particular vector.

01:11:23.640 --> 01:11:27.860
So look, you're talking about
the most general Hamiltonian,

01:11:27.860 --> 01:11:31.280
and you're saying it's
most easily understood

01:11:31.280 --> 01:11:35.200
as g not multiplying
the identity, and that g

01:11:35.200 --> 01:11:37.525
vector multiplying
the sigma vector.

01:11:40.220 --> 01:11:44.870
So on the other hand, g is this.

01:11:44.870 --> 01:11:51.040
So this is also g not 1
plus g times n dot sigma.

01:11:57.120 --> 01:11:59.945
But let's continue here.

01:12:07.320 --> 01:12:09.930
We know how to
solve this problem.

01:12:09.930 --> 01:12:12.330
And you can say,
well, all right.

01:12:12.330 --> 01:12:16.740
I have to diagonalize this
matrix, find the eigen vectors,

01:12:16.740 --> 01:12:20.612
find the eigenvalues,
and all that.

01:12:20.612 --> 01:12:23.470
But you've done all that work.

01:12:23.470 --> 01:12:25.830
It's already been done.

01:12:25.830 --> 01:12:28.120
What were the eigen states?

01:12:28.120 --> 01:12:33.620
Well, n dot sigma,
the eigen states

01:12:33.620 --> 01:12:39.200
were the end states, the
spin states, n plus minus.

01:12:39.200 --> 01:12:44.090
And they were plus minus
n comma plus minus.

01:12:47.630 --> 01:12:53.720
Remember that S
is H over 2 sigma.

01:12:53.720 --> 01:13:01.840
So this corresponds to n dot
S on n plus minus equal plus

01:13:01.840 --> 01:13:06.080
minus H bar over 2
n plus minus, which

01:13:06.080 --> 01:13:09.560
might be the form in which
you remember it better.

01:13:09.560 --> 01:13:14.180
But the sigma
matrices, n dot sigma

01:13:14.180 --> 01:13:17.660
is diagonalized
precisely by this thing.

01:13:17.660 --> 01:13:22.810
So in fact, you never have
to diagonalize this matrix.

01:13:22.810 --> 01:13:25.760
It's already been done for you.

01:13:25.760 --> 01:13:30.060
And these are the eigen
states of this Hamiltonian.

01:13:30.060 --> 01:13:37.650
And what is the value of
the energy on n plus minus?

01:13:37.650 --> 01:13:44.570
Well, energy on n plus minus
is g not times 1 plus g n

01:13:44.570 --> 01:13:48.985
dot sigma on the n plus minus.

01:13:51.920 --> 01:13:55.790
And g not times 1
here on this state

01:13:55.790 --> 01:14:03.830
is g not plus g n dot sigma,
the thing is plus minus.

01:14:03.830 --> 01:14:11.250
So plus minus g, n plus minus.

01:14:11.250 --> 01:14:15.680
So in fact, you
have the energies,

01:14:15.680 --> 01:14:17.960
and you have the eigen vectors.

01:14:17.960 --> 01:14:31.076
So the eigen states are n plus
with energy equal g not plus g

01:14:31.076 --> 01:14:38.670
and n minus with energy
equal g not minus g.

01:14:44.580 --> 01:14:48.220
So what we did by inventing
the Pauli matrices

01:14:48.220 --> 01:14:50.530
and inventing spin
states and all

01:14:50.530 --> 01:14:55.230
that was solve for
you the most general 2

01:14:55.230 --> 01:14:58.930
by 2 Hamiltonian,
Hermitian Hamiltonian.

01:14:58.930 --> 01:15:01.440
If you have a 2 by
2 Hermitian matrix,

01:15:01.440 --> 01:15:04.320
you don't have to
diagonalize it by hand.

01:15:04.320 --> 01:15:07.760
You know the answers
are this state.

01:15:10.510 --> 01:15:12.470
And how do you
build those states?

01:15:12.470 --> 01:15:16.470
Well, you know what n is
because you know the g's.

01:15:16.470 --> 01:15:20.210
If you know the three g's,
you know what the vector g is.

01:15:20.210 --> 01:15:22.000
You know what the vector n is.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:24.640
You know what this g is as well.

01:15:24.640 --> 01:15:26.630
And therefore, with
a vector n, you

01:15:26.630 --> 01:15:30.170
construct this state, as
you know already very well.

01:15:30.170 --> 01:15:34.060
And given that you
know g and g not,

01:15:34.060 --> 01:15:41.040
well the energies are
this, at the splitting

01:15:41.040 --> 01:15:44.800
is 2g between those states.

01:15:44.800 --> 01:15:46.560
This is the ground state.

01:15:46.560 --> 01:15:50.180
This is the excited state.

01:15:50.180 --> 01:15:53.370
Splitting two g's, so you
look at the Hamiltonian,

01:15:53.370 --> 01:15:57.080
and you say, what's the
splitting between the two eigen

01:15:57.080 --> 01:15:59.020
states of this.

01:15:59.020 --> 01:16:05.620
You just take this numbers,
compute g, and multiply by 2.

01:16:05.620 --> 01:16:09.250
Now, last thing
that you would want

01:16:09.250 --> 01:16:13.720
to do with this Hamiltonian
is time evolution.

01:16:13.720 --> 01:16:18.380
So what do we say
about time evolution?

01:16:18.380 --> 01:16:25.700
Well, we have here
H is equal to this.

01:16:31.640 --> 01:16:48.530
And we also had omega L dot
S. So omega L dot S in here

01:16:48.530 --> 01:16:51.950
should be identified with this.

01:16:51.950 --> 01:17:00.020
So sigma and S, as you remember,
S is equal H bar over 2 sigma.

01:17:00.020 --> 01:17:07.150
So this term can be
written as g vector sigma.

01:17:07.150 --> 01:17:09.790
In fact, this is
better from here.

01:17:09.790 --> 01:17:14.790
g vector sigma, and
sigma is H bar over 2S.

01:17:19.430 --> 01:17:21.640
I got a 2 over H bar.

01:17:25.540 --> 01:17:28.190
2 over H bar S.

01:17:28.190 --> 01:17:37.685
So from here, g dot sigma is
2g over H bar S. And remember,

01:17:37.685 --> 01:17:44.370
a Hamiltonian for a
spin system, whatever's

01:17:44.370 --> 01:17:47.830
multiplying the vector
that is multiplying S

01:17:47.830 --> 01:17:52.970
is omega L. So in
this system-- I

01:17:52.970 --> 01:18:00.850
will write it like that--
omega L is 2g over H bar.

01:18:04.400 --> 01:18:07.920
And this is a great
physical help.

01:18:07.920 --> 01:18:12.080
Because now that
you have this, I

01:18:12.080 --> 01:18:14.530
should remark this
part of the Hamiltonian

01:18:14.530 --> 01:18:16.840
is the one that does procession.

01:18:16.840 --> 01:18:21.640
A part proportional to the
identity cannot do procession,

01:18:21.640 --> 01:18:27.000
is just a constant term that
produces a constant phase,

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:28.490
just produces a pure phase.

01:18:28.490 --> 01:18:31.060
That's a change,
an overall phase

01:18:31.060 --> 01:18:33.310
that doesn't change the state.

01:18:33.310 --> 01:18:39.230
You would have an extra factor
of e to the minus i times

01:18:39.230 --> 01:18:44.260
that constant, g
not t over H bar,

01:18:44.260 --> 01:18:46.280
multiplying all the states.

01:18:46.280 --> 01:18:49.970
Doesn't change the action
on plus or minus state.

01:18:49.970 --> 01:18:52.120
It's an overall phase.

01:18:52.120 --> 01:18:56.960
This term in the Hamiltonian
is almost never very important.

01:18:56.960 --> 01:19:00.130
It doesn't do anything
to the physical states,

01:19:00.130 --> 01:19:02.550
just gives them pure phases.

01:19:02.550 --> 01:19:05.200
And this term is the
thing that matters.

01:19:05.200 --> 01:19:08.590
So now with this
Hamiltonian, because g

01:19:08.590 --> 01:19:11.570
dot sigma is the form
of the Hamiltonian,

01:19:11.570 --> 01:19:15.350
and we've identified this
physical phenomenon of Larmor

01:19:15.350 --> 01:19:21.170
frequency, if you know your
vector g for any Hamiltonian,

01:19:21.170 --> 01:19:25.160
this might be the [INAUDIBLE]
for ammonia molecule,

01:19:25.160 --> 01:19:28.830
then you know how the
states evolve in time.

01:19:28.830 --> 01:19:31.840
Because you represent the state.

01:19:31.840 --> 01:19:35.370
You have one state
and a second state.

01:19:35.370 --> 01:19:37.950
You think of the one
state as the plus

01:19:37.950 --> 01:19:40.420
of a spin, the minus of a spin.

01:19:40.420 --> 01:19:43.890
And then you know that this
is processing with this Larmor

01:19:43.890 --> 01:19:45.840
frequency.

01:19:45.840 --> 01:19:50.050
So it may sound a little
abstract at this moment,

01:19:50.050 --> 01:19:54.130
but this gives you the way
to evolve any arbitrary state

01:19:54.130 --> 01:19:55.290
intuitively.

01:19:55.290 --> 01:19:58.530
You know the vector
V where it points.

01:19:58.530 --> 01:20:02.500
You know where your state points
in the configuration space.

01:20:02.500 --> 01:20:06.240
And you have a physical picture
of what it does in time.

01:20:06.240 --> 01:20:08.350
It's always precessing.

01:20:08.350 --> 01:20:12.930
Therefore, the dynamics of
a two-state system in time

01:20:12.930 --> 01:20:16.410
is always procession, and
that's what we have to learn.

